<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><strong>How to read this page.</strong> Preliminary research on the Payr=
oll Distributions widget, with insights and a recommended design direction.=
 Part A is what the widget is and does today (checked live). Part B is who =
uses it and what the market and the SME tell us. Part C is the brief: jobs =
to be done, scenarios, constraints, the significant design decisions and th=
eir rationale, a review of the current redesign attempt, and prioritized ne=
eds. Status marks: <span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visu=
al-refresh aui-lozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span>, <span class=3D"status=
-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-complete">DESKTOP=
 RESEARCH</span>, <span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visua=
l-refresh aui-lozenge-progress">SME INTERVIEW</span>, <span class=3D"status=
-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-current">TO CONFI=
RM</span>. Sources at the bottom.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-PartA.Whatexiststoday">Part A. What exists t=
oday</h1>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-1.WhatPayrollDistributionsis">1. What Payrol=
l Distributions is</h2>
<p>The widget shows a breakdown of payroll spend by <strong>compensation ty=
pe</strong> across a chosen date range: how the total paid splits across ca=
tegories like salary, hourly, housing allowance, and benefits, for any peri=
od the user picks. Its grain is the category summary (one row per compensat=
ion type), not a raw list of individual checks. Confirmed live on beta1: re=
al categories render as org-defined labels, such as "AA Aid" and "Administr=
ation Staff". These labels ( =E2=80=9CCompensation Types=E2=80=9D) are mana=
ged under Payroll&gt;Modify&gt;CompensationInformation</p>
<p><strong>What the grand total means.</strong> The total is the sum of eve=
ry distribution paid within the selected date range, for the current compan=
y, across all compensation categories. It is not a single category, and it =
is not an "as of today" balance: it is money that flowed out over a span of=
 time. With the default range (1 January to today) it reads as total payrol=
l paid year to date; narrow the range to a month and it reads as total paid=
 that month. The category rows are the breakdown; the grand total is their =
sum. This flow-not-balance nature is the root of the most important design =
decision on this page (Section 10).</p>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-complete">DESKTOP RESEARCH</span> <strong>Why compensation type is t=
he right lens.</strong> The category split is what makes this widget meanin=
gful rather than a bare total, because in church payroll the compensation c=
ategories carry the tax treatment. Ordained ministers have a dual tax statu=
s (employee for income tax, self-employed for Social Security and Medicare)=
, a designated housing allowance is income-tax-excluded but SECA-liable and=
 lands in W-2 Box 14, and categories differ in what they are subject to. So=
 a category is not just a label, it signals how that pay is taxed and repor=
ted, which is why an administrator reasons about payroll by category. This =
is context for why the grain is right; it is not a task the user performs h=
ere (there are no tax jobs in Section 6). Sources: <a href=3D"https://www.i=
rs.gov/taxtopics/tc417" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">IRS Topic =
417</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.irs.gov/faqs/interest-dividends-other-types=
-of-income/ministers-compensation-housing-allowance/ministers-compensation-=
housing-allowance" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">IRS housing all=
owance</a>, <a href=3D"https://churchshield.com/blog/how-do-churches-pay-th=
eir-employees/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ChurchShield</a>, =
<a href=3D"https://auxilio.partners/insights/understanding-the-dual-tax-sta=
tus-of-clergy" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Auxilio</a>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-2.Wherethedatacomesfrom">2. Where the data c=
omes from</h2>
<p>Original documentation, validated against Shelby's own dashboard referen=
ce. The widget totals the amount per compensation type for checks issued wi=
thin the selected date range. Voided checks and certain internal check type=
s are excluded, so figures reflect only real, valid payments. There is no c=
ache: every load or refresh queries live payroll records. Note for later de=
cisions: because PRHistory stores the actual check date of every processed =
payroll, the real pay dates an org has already run are available in the dat=
a.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1296" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 317.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 979.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Table</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>What it holds</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>PRHistory</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Payroll run records, each processed payroll including check date and che=
ck type</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>PRHistoryCompensation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The compensation line items within each run, including category and amou=
nt</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-3.Thewidgettoday">3. The widget today</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1296" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Behavior</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Status</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Left: a table listing each compensation category with its total amount f=
or the period, and a totals row (count of categories, overall sum). Seen li=
ve: two rows plus "Total 2 Distributions =C2=A35,090.63"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> (beta1)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Right: a pie chart "By Distributions", one segment per compensation cate=
gory, amount shown on hover only</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> (beta1)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Beginning and Ending date pickers. Beginning defaults to 1 January of th=
e current year, Ending to today. Both panels are intended to cover the same=
 range</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> (controls), both-panels-update <span c=
lass=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-cur=
rent">TO CONFIRM</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Refresh reruns the query for the current range. No drill-down: clicking =
a row or segment opens nothing</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-4.Liveaudit(15Jul2026)">4. Live audit (15 Ju=
l 2026)</h2>
<p>Two environments. Passes 1 and 2 on asmdev (company 101, empty of payrol=
l) covered structure, states, date persistence, and the Payroll module walk=
. Pass 3 on beta1.accounting.myamplify.io (company "1 Saint Michael Church"=
, populated) covered the widget with real data. Method throughout: DOM and =
accessibility-tree inspection plus interaction testing. The populated pass =
confirmed the accessibility findings on real data and settled the category-=
grain question; only both-panels-update-on-date-change remains genuinely op=
en.</p>
<p><strong>Populated data seen (beta1):</strong> two categories, "AA Aid" =
=C2=A3560.00 and "Administration Staff" =C2=A34,530.63, Total 2 Distributio=
ns =C2=A35,090.63, with a matching two-segment pie.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1296" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Finding</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Status</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Beginning and Ending date inputs are properly labeled, each with a "pick=
 date" button. Better than the Deposits On Hand widget's unlabeled filter</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Refresh is a plain link with <strong>no freshness timestamp</strong>. Co=
nsistent with the live-query design, but the user gets no "data as of" sign=
al</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>The grid is three separate HTML tables</strong> (header, body, t=
otals), cells exposed as generic nodes not th/td, confirmed on populated da=
ta. A screen reader gets a flat text stream with no column association betw=
een a category and its amount. WCAG 1.3.1 failure, same as Deposits On Hand=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> (beta1, populated)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Pie values are hover-only.</strong> On populated data the segmen=
t amounts live only in a hidden textbox feeding the JS renderer, absent fro=
m the accessibility tree. The table is the only accessible source of amount=
s, and it lacks column semantics. So a non-visual user has no reliable way =
to read the breakdown</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> (beta1, populated)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Empty state is "No records to display." with a blank Total Distributions=
 row: no explicit zero, no explanation, no recovery. A fresh org or an empt=
y range hits this immediately, so it is the widget's de facto first impress=
ion</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Category names are <strong>org-defined and unpredictable</strong> ("AA A=
id", "Administration Staff" on beta1), not a standard pay-type taxonomy</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> (beta1)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Currency renders from client or server culture, not the org: =C2=A3 show=
n on a US product, on <strong>real data</strong> not just the empty state. =
Date inputs likewise render dd/mm/yyyy. Same localization root-cause questi=
on as the Deposits On Hand audit</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span> (beta1)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The widget title links to the widget chooser (17 panels), not the Payrol=
l module</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>The date range persists across a page reload</strong> (asmdev, p=
ass 2). No reset on load. Logout/login persistence untested</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>The Payroll module has a read layer:</strong> View &gt; Earnings=
 Inquiry. Its filter is a single Employee picker plus check-date presets an=
d Regular/Manual/Voided toggles, so it is a <strong>per-employee earnings l=
ookup, not a distribution-level view</strong>. Relevant to drill-through (f=
lag F8)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Company context is remembered per module (asmdev): opening Payroll switc=
hed to company 100 while the dashboard ran 101, which is why the widget was=
 empty there. The widget reads the dashboard's active company</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-success">VERIFIED LIVE</span></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Still open: both-panels-update-on-date-change.</strong> On beta1=
 the totals did not change across date edits, but the ASP.NET date control =
may not have committed the programmatically set value before the postback, =
so this is inconclusive, not a negative result</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-current">TO CONFIRM</span> Needs a clean manual date pick or a datas=
et spanning multiple periods</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-PartB.Usersandmarket">Part B. Users and mark=
et</h1>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-5.Personas">5. Personas</h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-l=
ozenge-complete">DESKTOP RESEARCH</span> and <span class=3D"status-macro au=
i-lozenge aui-lozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-progress">SME INTERVIEW</s=
pan>. The primary persona is Ministry Brands Accounting's primary persona; =
payroll is run at the individual church, not at a headquarters.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1077" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Persona</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Relationship to this widget</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P1. Church bookkeeper or business administrator (primary)</stron=
g></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Runs payroll, often part time or wearing several hats. Needs to see what=
 was paid, in what categories, and whether it looks right. Frequently not a=
 payroll specialist, so clergy tax complexity is a burden they carry, not a=
n expertise they hold (<a href=3D"https://churchshield.com/blog/how-do-chur=
ches-pay-their-employees/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ChurchS=
hield</a>). This is Ministry Brands Accounting's primary persona.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P2. Senior/lead pastor or executive pastor (oversight)</strong><=
/p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Reviews total comp cost and its distribution for budgeting and board rep=
orting. Wants the "where did payroll go" answer without reading a register.=
 Thinks in calendar and fiscal terms (year to date, this year), not pay run=
s.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P3. Treasurer / finance committee (governance)</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Volunteer oversight. Uses category totals to sanity-check budget vs actu=
al and to answer board questions. Often relies on reports rather than loggi=
ng in, so access for this persona is partly a licensing question.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>P4. External bookkeeper or payroll service (contextual)</strong>=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Some churches outsource. When they do, this widget is a quick internal c=
heck against what the service reports.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"ssrxh0ft6y">Note the split that matters for design=
: P1 thinks operationally (by pay run, "did the last payroll look right"), =
while P2 and P3 think in calendar and fiscal periods ("what have we spent t=
his year"). The period control has to serve both mindsets. </span>This is c=
entral to Section 10.</p>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-6.Jobstobedone,andwhethertheproductsupportst=
hemtoday">6. Jobs to be done, and whether the product supports them today</=
h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
