<span data-colorid=3D"yc4ssfk90n">NEED TO GROOM THIS AND MAKE DECISION</spa=
n></p>
<h3 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-10.5Adedicatedtrendchart:notapplicable(see10=
.3)">10.5 A dedicated trend chart: not applicable (see 10.3)</h3>
<p>A trend-over-time chart is a comparison element and is therefore covered=
 by the rejection in 10.3. Recorded separately only because the W03 mockup =
and earlier drafts raised it: it is out of scope for the same two reasons.<=
/p>
<h3 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-10.6Detail-on-demandshouldstayinsidethewidge=
t">10.6 Detail-on-demand should stay inside the widget</h3>
<p><strong>Decision:</strong> serve JTBD 5 (see the detail behind a categor=
y) within the widget's own focus overlay, not by linking out. Earnings Inqu=
iry cannot be the destination: it is per-employee, not per-distribution (Se=
ction 4, flag F8). The user need is to see what is behind a category total;=
 the constraint is no new pages. How that view looks is for design. <a clas=
s=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention current-user-mention" data-account-id=
=3D"712020:c9d98ec9-c34d-4652-978c-957d632b2a23" href=3D"https://ministrybr=
ands.atlassian.net/wiki/people/712020:c9d98ec9-c34d-4652-978c-957d632b2a23?=
ref=3Dconfluence" target=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=3D"6600884232" =
data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" d=
ata-base-url=3D"https://ministrybrands.atlassian.net/wiki">Oisin Curran</a>=
 <a class=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-account-id=3D"712020:1d=
721d4a-5dc6-4a11-81b7-e415de2e5d78" href=3D"https://ministrybrands.atlassia=
n.net/wiki/people/712020:1d721d4a-5dc6-4a11-81b7-e415de2e5d78?ref=3Dconflue=
nce" target=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=3D"5556502538" data-linked-r=
esource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=
=3D"https://ministrybrands.atlassian.net/wiki">Feargal Phelan</a> <span dat=
a-colorid=3D"l87mkj6d97">My take is this one would be a nice to have for fo=
llow-up improvement - not in scope for this first iteration - let me know. =
Jo</span></p>
<h3 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-10.7Shelldependencytoraise">10.7 Shell depen=
dency to raise</h3>
<p>The canonical widget shell documents its period vocabulary as a fixed ca=
lendar list (Week / Month / Quarter / Fiscal year / Calendar year). Calenda=
r spans (10.2) fit that vocabulary, so the recommended direction stays with=
in the shell. Worth noting for the Figma / shell session: any future flow-t=
ype widget wanting a non-calendar cadence unit would need a shell change.</=
p>
<h3 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-10.8Howthecontentcouldmapontothewidgetviews(=
suggestion)">10.8 How the content could map onto the widget views (suggesti=
on)</h3>
<p>The views (glance, detail, explore) and the focus overlay are a settled =
platform decision (see 9.3; source of truth is the <a href=3D"https://www.f=
igma.com/design/3sw45aVcngFAmpbP6cfrXP/%E2%9D%87%EF%B8%8F--Pathway-Design-S=
ystem--Master-File--MB-2.0-?node-id=3D40009622-39702" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">widget shell in Figma</a>). The views are a content-dep=
th vector, not sizes: each can span different column counts by breakpoint. =
What content sits at each view is a design call, but here is a mapping sugg=
estion, offered because it follows from the jobs and the flow nature, for t=
he designer to accept or rework:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1200" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>View (established)</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>User goal at this view</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>What could carry it, and why (suggestion)</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Glance</strong> (KPI tile)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>"What did we pay this period?"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A headline number (the grand total for the selected period), minimal con=
trol (the period control), and optionally a small interactive mini chart. T=
his serves the pulse-check job (JTBD 1). No trend or comparison element (10=
.3), so any mini chart shows within-period composition, not movement over t=
ime</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Detail</strong> (more controls, more data views)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>"How did it split?"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>More controls and more than one way to view the data (for example a tabl=
e and a distribution view), plus the period control. This is where category=
 composition (JTBD 2) is served, with amounts and share as text per the acc=
essibility constraint</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Explore</strong> (full screen width, same controls as detail)</p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>"Let me see it clearly, or two ways at once"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Same controls as detail, but full width gives room for complex charts to=
 render with more clarity and for two data views side by side, for example =
the table and a donut together. Useful here because exact amounts (table) a=
nd proportion (donut) are both wanted, and seeing them together supports a =
board- or budget-prep read</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Focus</strong> (isolate-and-focus overlay, not a view)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>"What is behind this category?"</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The widget isolated in place to give a category room to expand to the ch=
ecks or employees behind it (JTBD 5), staying inside the widget per 10.6. N=
ot navigation to another page <span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-l=
ozenge-visual-refresh aui-lozenge-error">NOT IN SCOPE</span> <a class=3D"co=
nfluence-userlink user-mention current-user-mention" data-account-id=3D"712=
020:c9d98ec9-c34d-4652-978c-957d632b2a23" href=3D"https://ministrybrands.at=
lassian.net/wiki/people/712020:c9d98ec9-c34d-4652-978c-957d632b2a23?ref=3Dc=
onfluence" target=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=3D"6600884232" data-li=
nked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-bas=
e-url=3D"https://ministrybrands.atlassian.net/wiki">Oisin Curran</a> <a cla=
ss=3D"confluence-userlink user-mention" data-account-id=3D"712020:1d721d4a-=
5dc6-4a11-81b7-e415de2e5d78" href=3D"https://ministrybrands.atlassian.net/w=
iki/people/712020:1d721d4a-5dc6-4a11-81b7-e415de2e5d78?ref=3Dconfluence" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" data-linked-resource-id=3D"5556502538" data-linked-resource=
-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"userinfo" data-base-url=3D"http=
s://ministrybrands.atlassian.net/wiki">Feargal Phelan</a> let=E2=80=99s con=
firm on this one</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>This mapping is a starting point tied to the jobs, not a specification.<=
/p>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-11.Reviewoftheproposedredesign(WidgetMockups=
v3,W03)">11. Review of the proposed redesign (Widget Mockups v3, W03)</h2>
<p>Source: <a href=3D"https://oisin-curran-mb.github.io/Dashboard_Project/M=
ock_work/Dashboard%20Widget%20Mockups.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"=
nofollow">Dashboard Widget Mockups v3, W03</a>, reviewed 15 Jul 2026. <stro=
ng>What holds up:</strong> bars with visible values retire the hover-only p=
ie; the view ladder trims rows sensibly; the "Paid, not owed" framing is ri=
ght; the open-items discipline is exactly right for a locked doc. <strong>F=
lags before it locks:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1077" data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenc=
eTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>#</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Flag</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>What to do</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Default view is built on an unconfirmed Department dimension (their own =
open item)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Whether history compensation lines carry a department is unconfirmed. Se=
t the fallback now: if department cannot be derived, default to compensatio=
n-category rows (today's grain). Do not lock a view that may be unbuildable=
</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The Pay Period model is a scheduling feature in a filter's clothes (back=
ward-count presets, a recurring flag, per-department blocks)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Section 10 supersedes this. The period need is calendar spans plus alway=
s-available custom (10.2). Cut the recurring flag and per-department schedu=
ling; they belong to payroll processing, not a read widget. Pay-group scopi=
ng is deferred (10.4)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The mockup proposes a prior-period comparison</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Comparison is rejected for this widget (10.3): trend and delta elements =
are out of scope. Drop the comparison from the lock. If it is ever revisite=
d, the three-paycheck-month effect makes equal-basis alignment mandatory</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F4</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Confirmed live.</strong> The fixed pay-type list is invented; ca=
tegories are org-defined. Beta1 showed "AA Aid", "Administration Staff"</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Design for variable category names and counts. If a drill ever changes w=
hat a row means, signpost the change</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F5</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Widget states absent from the writeup</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Apply the Section 9.2 states: entitlement, rights, empty, loading, error=
</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F6</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>"Top 3 / top 5" trimming contradicts the fixed-alphabetical sort spec</p=
></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If a small view shows top rows, the sort must be amount-descending. Alph=
abetical top-3 is meaningless</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F7</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Accessibility unaddressed; the current widget already fails table semant=
ics and hover-only values on real data</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The redesign must actively fix this, not inherit it. See the accessibili=
ty constraint (9.3)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>F8</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Drill destination: Earnings Inquiry exists but is per-employee, not per-=
distribution (verified live). The SME confirms clients love report-style dr=
ill</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Keep detail inside the widget's focus overlay (10.6), not a link out to =
Earnings Inquiry</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Minor: several W03 entries are dated 2026-07-16 (tomorrow at review); wo=
rth correcting.</p>
<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-12.Gapsandprioritizedimprovements">12. Gaps =
and prioritized improvements</h2>
<p>Impact =3D severity times reach. Reach is supported by the SME signal th=
at Payroll is a core, well-liked module (8b). Effort: S =3D copy/label/stat=
e text, M =3D rework in the existing surface, L =3D new data exposure or fr=
amework work. The last two columns record evidence: whether the item has be=
en usability-tested, and what user research supports it. Everything here is=
 framed as a need to meet, not a solution to build.</p>
