<h2 id=3D"PayrollDistributions-13.Openquestionsandnextsteps">13. Open quest=
ions and next steps</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Pay group is deferred (10.4).</strong> Before it can be designed=
, a Value Labs investigation needs to establish the payroll data model: wha=
t a pay group is, how it relates to pay type and compensation type, how an =
employee maps to a pay group, and whether a historical distribution record =
(PRHistory / PRHistoryCompensation) carries a pay-group key at all (8c). Th=
is is a prerequisite, not a quick check.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Both-panels-update-on-date-change: confirm with a clean manual date pick=
 or a multi-period dataset that changing the range updates table and pie to=
gether.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Does a Department dimension exist on or via PRHistory / PRHistoryCompens=
ation? Blocks flag F1. (Home Department is a field on the employee record, =
seen live; whether it reaches the distribution history is the open part.)</=
p></li>
<li>
<p>Localization root cause (org vs server vs browser culture), shared with =
the Deposits On Hand audit.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Entitlement and rights detection for the widget states (see the two ques=
tions to Oisin and Feargal in 9.2).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Raise the period-vocabulary point with the Figma / shell session (10.7).=
</p></li>
</ul>
